  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  40 years or older at time of eligibility screening;

          -  Body mass index 25.0-44.9 kg/m2 (also see Figure 2);

          -  Smoked more than 10 pack-years of cigarettes;

          -  Shortness of breath;

          -  COPD;

          -  Able to participate fully in all study protocol/procedures including written informed
             consent process.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Inability to speak, read, or understand English;

          -  Active weight loss interventions;

          -  Expected weight loss because of alternate explanations, such as from illness;

          -  Unable to ambulate to weight scale for weight measurement;

          -  Safety and/or adherence concerns due to severe physical or mental health issues or
             life expectancy &lt;24 months;

          -  Pregnant, lactating, or planning to become pregnant during the study period;

          -  Participation in other intervention studies.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
